14/12/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- EUFOR Commander, Brigadier General Gian Marco Chiarini and BiH Defence Minister Nikola Radovanovic agreed on Tuesday (13 December) that full co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal, including the arrest of Radovan Karadzic and Ratko Mladic, is a shared priority for their institutions. They also discussed mechanisms to enhance collaboration between EUFOR and the BiH armed forces. (Nezavisne novine - 14/12/05; PBS BiH, Fena, RS Government Web site, RTRS - 13/12/05)
